Vheadline
p2
VSinging in one voice
p3
sVnews
p4
VUnder the auspices of Department of Culture and Bhakta Ramadas College of Music and Dance, an educative programme was presented at the college venue marking the Jayanthi of M.S. Subbulakshmi. The whole programme was called asSangeetharchana.The entire show was designed in such a way that the students win over stage fear, gain confidence and display their skills in front of an audience.The audience included students, parents and some music lovers.  It was a pleasant sight to watch 15 children between the ages of five and ten, singing in chorus.They sangsarali swaras,javali, padamandtillana, all in bits that lasted more than 20 minutes. Haripriya of the famous Hyderabad sister-duo, Lalitha and Haripriya, a lecturer in the college, conceptualised the whole show with the initiative taken by the principal of the college Duddu Sitaramayya. Haripriya was also seen personally conducting the show, guiding them to perfection. The children presented this part with zest and with one voice. Students playing the violin, veena and mridangam too displayed talent. They were given 14 compositions. Later, senior students Manda Srinivas and M. Sriramachandra took part in a vocal duet.The repertoire\u000aincluded Sri Mahaganapathim\u000ain Athana of\u000aMysore Maharaja, Ragam-\u000aTanam - Pallavi in Hindolam,\u000aand a Ranjani raga\u000achain based on a song\u000aRanjani, Niranjani,\u000aSivaranjani.
